The paper discusses routing protocols in mobile ad-hoc networks (MANETs) and vehicular ad-hoc networks (VANETs), which are both subfields of computer networking and fall under the cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) category. The paper also mentions simulation work, which suggests that it may fall under the cs.MA (multi-agent systems) category. Additionally, the paper discusses modifications to the routing protocols, which could fall under the cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) or cs.IT (information theory) categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the routing protocols, which could fall under the cs.SI (social and information networks) category.
